prompt:
List down the different types of vegetables you can grow in your garden, and give a brief description of each.
In my garden, I grow a variety of vegetables including tomatoes, bell peppers, cucumbers, lettuce heads, zucchinis, pumpkins, eggplants, okra pods, cabbage heads, and carrot roots. These vegetables not only add nutritious value to my meals but also contribute to the aesthetics of my garden.
